77. From the earliest times the free population of Rome consisted of three classes :—

1. Patricians, who formed the Roman nobility.

2. Plebeians who formed the great body of the common people.

3. Clients‚ who were without political rights, and were dependent for protection on patrons to whom they owed allegiance.
